maxMonthlyBudget.nanos.description:
Number of nano (10^-9) units of the amount.
The value must be between -999,999,999 and +999,999,999 inclusive.
If `units` is positive, `nanos` must be positive or zero.
If `units` is zero, `nanos` can be positive, zero, or negative.
If `units` is negative, `nanos` must be negative or zero.
For example $-1.75 is represented as `units`=-1 and `nanos`=-750,000,000.

Date.description:
Represents a whole or partial calendar date, e.g. a birthday. The time of day
and time zone are either specified elsewhere or are not significant. The date
is relative to the Proleptic Gregorian Calendar. This can represent:

* A full date, with non-zero year, month and day values
* A month and day value, with a zero year, e.g. an anniversary
* A year on its own, with zero month and day values
* A year and month value, with a zero day, e.g. a credit card expiration date

Related types are google.type.TimeOfDay and `google.protobuf.Timestamp`.

day.description:
Day of month. Must be from 1 to 31 and valid for the year and month, or 0
if specifying a year by itself or a year and month where the day is not
significant.

month.description:
Month of year. Must be from 1 to 12, or 0 if specifying a year without a
month and day.

year.description:
Year of date. Must be from 1 to 9999, or 0 if specifying a date without
a year.

Money.description: Represents an amount of money with its currency type.

currencyCode.description: The 3-letter currency code defined in ISO 4217.

nanos.description:
Number of nano (10^-9) units of the amount.
The value must be between -999,999,999 and +999,999,999 inclusive.
If `units` is positive, `nanos` must be positive or zero.
If `units` is zero, `nanos` can be positive, zero, or negative.
If `units` is negative, `nanos` must be negative or zero.
For example $-1.75 is represented as `units`=-1 and `nanos`=-750,000,000.

units.description:
The whole units of the amount.
For example if `currencyCode` is `"USD"`, then 1 unit is one US dollar.

adwordsUrl.description: URL to the customer's AdWords page.

eligibilityDaysLeft.description: Days the customer is still eligible.

getYAmount.description: Formatted Get Y amount with currency code.

spendXAmount.description: Formatted Spend X amount with currency code.

OptIns.description: A set of opt-ins for a user.

marketComm.description:
An opt-in about receiving email from Partners marketing teams. Includes
member-only events and special promotional offers for Google products.

performanceSuggestions.description:
An opt-in about receiving email with customized AdWords campaign management
tips.

phoneContact.description: An opt-in to allow recieivng phone calls about their Partners account.

physicalMail.description: An opt-in to receive special promotional gifts and material in the mail.

specialOffers.description: An opt-in about receiving email regarding new features and products.

PublicProfile.description: Basic information from a public profile.

displayImageUrl.description: The URL to the main display image of the public profile. Being deprecated.

displayName.description: The display name of the public profile.

id.description: The ID which can be used to retrieve more details about the public profile.

profileImage.description: The URL to the main profile image of the public profile.

url.description: The URL of the public profile.

Rank.description: Information related to ranking of results.

value.description: The numerical value of the rank.

id.description: The ID of the reCaptcha challenge.

response.description: The response to the reCaptcha challenge.

locale.description: Locale to use for the current request.

trafficSource.description: Source of traffic for the current request.

userOverrides.description:

request. These are only honored by whitelisted products.

ResponseMetadata.description: Common data that is in each API response.

badgeSpecialization.description: The specialization this status is for.

TrafficSource.description: Source of traffic for the current request.

trafficSourceId.description:
Identifier to indicate where the traffic comes from.
An identifier has multiple letters created by a team which redirected the
traffic to us.

trafficSubId.description:
Second level identifier to indicate where the traffic comes from.
An identifier has multiple letters created by a team which redirected the
traffic to us.

User.description: A resource representing a user of the Partners platform.

afaInfoShared.description:
Whether or not the user has opted to share their Academy for Ads info with
Google Partners.

availableAdwordsManagerAccounts.description:
This is the list of AdWords Manager Accounts the user has edit access to.
If the user has edit access to multiple accounts, the user can choose the
preferred account and we use this when a personal account is needed. Can
be empty meaning the user has access to no accounts.
@OutputOnly

company.description:
The company that the user is associated with.
If not present, the user is not associated with any company.

companyVerificationEmail.description:
The email address used by the user used for company verification.
@OutputOnly

examStatus.description:
The list of exams the user ever taken. For each type of exam, only one
entry is listed.

internalId.description:
The internal user ID.
Only available for a whitelisted set of api clients.

lastAccessTime.description:
The most recent time the user interacted with the Partners site.
@OutputOnly

primaryEmails.description:
The list of emails the user has access to/can select as primary.
@OutputOnly

profile.description:
The profile information of a Partners user, contains all the directly
editable user information.

publicProfile.description: Information about a user's external public profile outside Google Partners.

UserOverrides.description:
Values to use instead of the user's respective defaults. These are only
honored by whitelisted products.

ipAddress.description: IP address to use instead of the user's geo-located IP address.

userId.description: Logged-in user ID to impersonate instead of the user's ID.

UserProfile.description: The profile information of a Partners user.

address.description: The user's mailing address, contains multiple fields.

adwordsManagerAccount.description:
If the user has edit access to multiple accounts, the user can choose the
preferred account and it is used when a personal account is needed. Can
be empty.

channels.description: A list of ids representing which channels the user selected they were in.

emailAddress.description: The email address the user has selected on the Partners site as primary.

emailOptIns.description: The list of opt-ins for the user, related to communication preferences.

industries.description: A list of ids representing which industries the user selected.

jobFunctions.description: A list of ids represnting which job categories the user selected.

languages.description: The list of languages this user understands.

markets.description: A list of ids representing which markets the user was interested in.

migrateToAfa.description: Whether or not to migrate the user's exam data to Academy for Ads.

primaryCountryCode.description: The user's primary country, an ISO 2-character code.

profilePublic.description: Whether the user's public profile is visible to anyone with the URL.
